>\begin{align*}
\Delta \lambda &= 110^\circ+115^\circ \\
&= 225^\circ \\
&= \frac{5\pi}{4} \text{ rad}
\end{align*}
The radius of a circle of latitude $\phi$ is exactly $R\cos\phi$, where $R$ is the radius of the earth so the difference in longitudes is given by
$ \frac{R\pi}{4}=225^\circ\sin\phi $
*now solve this expression for $\phi$
>\begin{align*}
\frac{225^\circ\sin\phi}{\pi} &= \frac{\pi}{4} \\
